Class VariableSymbol

    • bramspr.symboltable.Symbol

        • bramspr.symboltable.VariableSymbol

  • public class VariableSymbol
extends ValueYielderSymbol
    Objects of this class are symbol table entries associated with variables in a Bramspr-program. Since all information we want to keep about variables is already specified in ValueYielderSymbol, this class is nothing more than a concrete subclass of that abstract class.

      • openingLabel

        public org.objectweb.asm.Label openingLabel
        A label marking the start of this variable's scope. This label is unique; if a variable is declared halfway a scope, the variable's scope is only half the surrounding scope.

      • closingLabel

        public org.objectweb.asm.Label closingLabel
        A label marking the end of this variable's scope. This label can be shared with other variables, if they are declared in the same scope.
